----#include !/util/array
function arrayUnique(a)
  hash = {}
  out = {}

  for _,v in pairs(a) do
    if (not hash[v]) then
      out[#out+1] = v
      hash[v] = true
    end
  end

  return out
end

function arrayHasValue (a, val)
    for index, value in ipairs(a) do
        if value == val then
            return true
        end
    end

    return false
end

function arraySort(a)
  table.sort(a, function (left, right)
    return left < right
  end)
  return a
end

function arraySortTables(a, prop)
  table.sort(a, function (left, right)
    return left[prop] < right[prop]
  end)
  return a
end

function arrayMerge(a1, a2)
  for _,v in pairs(a2) do
    table.insert(a1, v)
  end
  return arrayUnique(a1);
end

function arrayRandomUnique(a, numElements)
  math.randomseed(os.time())
  pickedIndexes= {}
  pickedElements= {}
  for i=1,numElements do
    while(arrayHasValue(pickedIndexes, selected) or selected == nil) do
      selected = math.random(#a)
    end
    pickedIndexes[#pickedIndexes+1] = selected
    pickedElements[#pickedElements+1] = a[selected]
  end
  return pickedElements
end

function arrayPrint(a)
  print(table.concat(a, ", "))
end

----#include !/dominion/card
Card =  {
  guid = "",
  cost = 0,
  debt = 0,
  potion = 0,
  types = {}
}

function Card:new (o)
  o = o or {}   -- create object if user does not provide one
  setmetatable(o, self)
  self.__index = self
  return o
end

function Card:setup (obj, position, numCards)
  numCards = numCards or 10 -- Default, spawn 10 cards total
  baseClone = obj.clone({ position = position, snap_to_grid = true })
  baseClone.setRotation({0,180,0})
  deck = baseClone.clone({ position = { position[1], position[2] + 1, position[3] }})
  for i=1,numCards-2 do
    clone = obj.clone({ position = { position[1], position[2] + 1 + (0.1*i), position[3] }})
    deck = deck.putObject(clone)
  end
  baseClone.putObject(deck)
end

----#include cards/index

-- From left to right, top to bottom
supplyPositions = {
  {-8.00, 1.14, -3.00},
  {-4.00, 1.14, -3.00},
  {0.00, 1.14, -3.00},
  {4.00, 1.14, -3.00},
  {8.00, 1.14, -3.00},
  {-8.00, 1.14, -9.00},
  {-4.00, 1.14, -9.00},
  {0.00, 1.14, -9.00},
  {4.00, 1.14, -9.00},
  {8.00, 1.14, -9.00}
}

function setup()
  selectedCards = arrayRandomUnique(SUPPLY_ELIGIBLE_CARDS, 10)
  sortedCards = arraySortTables(selectedCards, "cost")
  for index,card in pairs(sortedCards) do
    obj = getObjectFromGUID(card.guid)
    card:setup(obj, supplyPositions[index])
  end
end

----#include !/dominion/setup

function onLoad()
  params = {
      click_function = "setup",
      function_owner = self,
      label          = "",
      position       = {0, 0.3, 0},
      rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
      width          = 600,
      height         = 600,
      font_size      = 340,
      color          = {0,0,0,0},
      font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
      tooltip        = "Set up a new game of Dominion.",
  }
  self.createButton(params)
end
